    • User

      public User​(UserRole role, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String surname, long seed)
      Creates a dummy User object for testing purposes. NOTE: This constructor is used to specifically test the random ID functionality.
      Parameters:
      role - the User's role. This should be predefined as the subclass _role variable.
      name - the User's name.
      surname - the User's surname.
      seed - the pseudo-random generator seed. This ensures repeatable random generation.

    • User

      public User​(UserRole role, java.lang.String idNumber, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String surname, Address address, java.lang.String password) throws OutOfRangeException, IdClashException
      Creates a bare dummy User object for testing purposes. The name and surname are used to provide another element of individuality to increase ease of testing rather than just looking at IDs.
      Parameters:
      role - the User's role. This should be predefined as the subclass _role variable.
      idNumber - the User's ID number. This will be added to the User role string to create the User ID.
      name - the User's name.
      surname - the User's surname.
      Throws:
      OutOfRangeException
      IdClashException
